comment: Johnson (MIA) maintains legal guarding position on Porzingis (NYK) and deflects the ball away.

Baker (NYK) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Johnson (MIA) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of MIA possession is overturned and NYK are awarded possession.
Dragic (MIA) makes marginal contact with Baker (NYK) that does not affect his SQBR.
Porzingis (NYK) makes marginal contact with Dragic (MIA) on the screen.
Johnson (MIA) cleanly strips the ball from Porzingis (NYK) on the driving shot attempt.
[Observable in enhanced video] Hernangomez (NYK) moves his pivot foot.
Whiteside (MIA) makes marginal contact with Hernangomez (NYK) on the driving shot attempt.
Whiteside (MIA) sets the screen on Baker (NYK) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Johnson (MIA) and Vujacic (NYK) make incidental contact with one another attempting to retrieve the loose ball.
Whiteside (MIA) sets the screen on Lee (NYK) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Vujacic (NYK) makes contact to Johnson's (MIA) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Hernangomez (NYK) sets the screen on Johnson (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Porzingis (NYK) sets the screen on Dragic (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Dragic (MIA) maintains legal guarding position on the drive to the basket by Baker (NYK).
Johnson (MIA) legally contests the driving shot attempt by Hernangomez (NYK) and any contact is considered incidental.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of MIA possession stands.
Baker (NYK) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Dragic (MIA) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Whiteside (MIA) committed offensive basket interference is confirmed.

Holiday (NYK) legally contests Ellington's (MIA) shot attempt.
